Copy the appropriate script to /etc/init.d/drproject

If your system is not listed here, the debian script is
a safe default.

Once the script has been copied, add it to the default
runlevel.

Debian/Ubuntu:
    update-rc.d drproject defaults

Gentoo:
    rc-update add drproject default

Fedora/Redhat:
    /sbin/chkconfig --add drproject

Others:
    ln -s /etc/init.d/drproject /etc/rc0.d/S99drproject # Shutdown
    ln -s /etc/init.d/drproject /etc/rc3.d/S99drproject # No X
    ln -s /etc/init.d/drproject /etc/rc5.d/S99drproject # X
    ln -s /etc/init.d/drproject /etc/rc6.d/S99drproject # Reboot
